9 (5) The Commission also shall adopt rules to do the following:
10 a. Establish the following regarding Commission records:
11 1. Conditions and procedures for public inspection and copying
12 of its information and official records, except such information
13 and records involving the privacy of individuals or that would
14 otherwise violate privacy laws under federal law and the laws
15 of the compacting states.
16 2. Procedures for sharing with federal and state agencies,
17 including law enforcement agencies, records and information
18 otherwise exempt from disclosure.
19 3. Guidelines for entering into agreements with federal and state
20 agencies to receive or exchange information or records subject
21 to nondisclosure and confidentiality provisions.
22 b. Provide a process for Commission review of submitted treatments and
23 therapeutic protocols for curing diseases that includes the following:
24 1. An opportunity for an appeal, not later than 30 days after a
25 rejection of a treatment or protocol for prize consideration, to
26 a review panel established under the Commission's dispute
27 resolution process.
28 2. Commission monitoring and review of treatment and protocol
29 effectiveness consistent with the cure criteria established by
30 the Commission for the particular disease.
31 3. Commission reconsideration, modification, or withdrawal of
32 approval of a treatment or protocol for prize consideration for
33 failure to continue to meet the cure criteria established by the
34 Commission for the particular disease.
35 c. Establish a dispute resolution process to resolve disputes or other
36 issues under the compact that may arise between two or more
37 compacting states or between the Commission and individuals or
38 entities who submit treatments and therapeutic protocols to cure
39 diseases, which process shall provide for:
40 1. Administrative review by a review panel appointed by the
41 Commission.
42 2. Judicial review of decisions issued after an administrative
43 review.
44 3. Qualifications to be appointed to a panel, due process
45 requirements, including notice and hearing procedures, and
46 any other procedure, requirement, or standard necessary to
47 provide adequate dispute resolution.
48 d. Establish and impose annual member dues on compacting states,
49 which shall be calculated based on the percentage of each compacting
50 state's population in relation to the population of all the compacting
51 states.
